    "body": "### Problem\n\nwhen i have nvim with open file and i put my computer to sleep and bring back up i find nvim completely frozen that i have to force close the terminal window, tab or split.\r\nthe terminal itself works fine because I've tested it with kitty and wezterm, it's only neovim that's frozen.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nopen a file with nvim\r\nput computer to sleep\r\nwake up computer\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nneovim be fine and i'am able to continue working.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1420+g9dc440400 & NVIM v0.9.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.0.2070\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nendeavourOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.30.1 & wezterm 20230712-072601-f4abf8fd\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color & (wezterm & kitty terminfos)\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
